{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1989 |Team=Arizona Wildcats | Image = | ImageSize = 120 |Conference=Pacific 10 Conference |ShortConference=Pac 10 |Division= |CoachRank= |APRank=25 |Record=8-4 |ConfRecord=5-3 |HeadCoach=[[Dick Tomey]] |OffCoach= |DefCoach= |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena=Arizona Stadium |Champion=Copper Bowl champions |BowlTourney=[[1989 Copper Bowl]] |BowlTourneyResult=Win, 17-10, vs. {{cfb link|year=1989|team=NC State Wolfpack|title=North Carolina State}} }} {{1989 Pacific-10 football standings}} The '''1989 Arizona Wildcats football team''' represented [[University of Arizona]] during the 1989 NCAA college football season. The offense scored 248 points while the defense allowed 178 points. Led by head coach Dick Tomey, the Wildcats participated in the [[1989 Copper Bowl|first Copper Bowl]].
